{
  "stem": "490.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So-- and I met my sister, and she and her husband and children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So she was the only one who survived.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And, of course, through circumstances, my sister went to Israel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And she started a new life in Israel with her family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I did not know anybody who cared for me or anybody who would-- would claim me as any connection with my life.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I-- when I was young, I never thought of it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I never-- I never even saw-- had a picture of my father or my mother.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't even know how they look like.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I might walk in the street and see the same face which my mother looked like, but I wouldn't-- wouldn't know.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So-- what was your question, again?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was-- it's just like you-- you-- you grow up, and you don't [BACKGROUND NOISE] you don't know any different.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You don't know-- like, not to compare, it is like when you see somebody who was born with one arm.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] To us, this man is handicapped.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But to somebody who has never had a-- he only lived-- he was born with one arm, to them it's normal.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Or a blind person.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "If you get-- God forbid, you lose an eye, you think is the world is coming to an end.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But people who never experienced the pleasure, or  the-- the-- the-- to be normal, to have both eyes and all-- to them it's-- you-- you-- you get used to it.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it is a part of life.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So to be an orphan-- I never asked why everybody has beautiful outfits for the holidays and I had to wear a second-hand pair of pants or-- or outfit.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, this was the way life is.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Everyone-- people look  different, and people live different.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
